fission track thermochronology laboratory stanford university fission track thermochronology laboratory home about research publications people equipment contact home fission track thermochronology and u th he thermochronology are methods for reconstructing the time temperature histories of rock samples in the upper 1 to 10 km of the earth's crust although the two methods are quite different from each other they yield highly complementary data and are best applied together for most application the fission track laboratory provides facilities and expertise for a wide range of potential studies in the fields of tectonics neotectonics basin and provenance analysis petroleum maturation ore deposits etc the noble gas laboratory provides facilities for complementary u th he analyses stanford university all rights reserved stanford ca 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
